Privacy Policy
Introduction
This policy informs visitors and users of our website and
app regarding our policies in respect of the collection,
use, sharing and disclosure of personal information
(
"personal information" as defined in POPI
). We are committed
to privacy practices in compliance with POPI.
Information collection and use
In order to use our service, we may require you to provide us with
certain personally identifiable information, and personal
information, including but not limited to: name, mobile number,
email address. We may also collect information through your social
media accounts such as Facebook, Google and Apple accounts. If you
use the Nearby location functionality, we collect your
geolocation. If you use our ESP Chat (or AskMyStreet)
functionality, we collect your geolocation. The information that
we collect will be retained by us and used as described in this
privacy policy and our terms.
We collect information directly from you when you provide
information on registration or otherwise communicate with us or
from your interaction with our services or when you use any
features or resources available on or through our website or app.
If a user of our services, provides information through the app
about you (as a third party), our platform collects the
information from our user. Our user is however contractually bound
to only share third party information with consent.
All processing of personal information relates to the services we
offer and enhancing your experience. Processing therefore includes
any required use relating to your application, account, use of the
services, analysing and monitoring use, product development,
working with authorities or other relevant parties, reporting
abuse or misconduct, and marketing. We do not sell personal
information.
Log Data
We want to inform you that whenever you use our service, in a case
of an error in the app we collect data and information (through
third party products) on your phone called Log Data. This Log Data
may include information such as your device Internet Protocol
("IP") address, device name, operating system version, the
configuration of the app when utilizing our service, the time and
date of your use of the service, and other statistics.
Cookies
Cookies are files with a small amount of data that are commonly
used as anonymous unique identifiers. These are sent to your
browser from the websites that you visit and are stored on your
device's internal memory.
The service does not use these "cookies" explicitly. However, the
app may use third party code and libraries that use "cookies" to
collect information and improve their services. You have the
option to either accept or refuse these cookies and know when a
cookie is being sent to your device. If you choose to refuse our
cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of our
service.
Service Providers
We may employ third-party companies and individuals for the
following reasons:
to facilitate our service;
to provide the service on our behalf;
to perform services related to our service; or
to assist us in analysing how our service is used and provide other support services to us.
These third parties have access to your personal information for
the sole purpose to perform services to us or on our behalf.
However, they are obligated in law not to disclose or use the
information for any other purpose and they only process the
information in terms of a contract with us
Disclosure of Personal information
Other than disclosure to service providers, we may disclose
information if the law allows or requires it from us, including
for example sharing with authorities, business partners in respect
of our business or the services.
If our service providers or business partners are located cross
border, we may share the information cross border, but at all
times in compliance with the POPI requirements for cross border
sharing of information.
Security
We value your trust in providing us your personal information,
thus we are striving to use commercially acceptable means of
protecting it. But remember that no method of transmission over
the internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure and
reliable, and we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
We implement appropriate technical and organisational security
measures in accordance with POPI, designed to protect personal
information against accidental or unlawful destruction, loss,
alteration, disclosure, access and other unlawful or unauthorised
forms of processing.
Links to Other Sites or Apps
This service may contain advertisements of third party products or
services or links to other sites. If you click on a third-party
link, you will be directed to that site or app. Note that these
external sites or apps are not operated or controlled by us.
Therefore, we strongly advise you to review the privacy policies
of these websites or apps before using it. We have no control over
and assume no responsibility for the content, privacy policies, or
practices of any third-party sites, apps or services and how they
process your personal information.
Children's Privacy
Our services are not aimed at minors and we do not knowingly
collect personally identifiable information from minors. All
personal information of minors provided to us, must be provided
with the consent of a guardian or parent.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Thus, you are
advised to review this page periodically for any changes. We will
